2. 2D PHYSICS-BASED MATCH ENGINE (REVOLUTIONARY)
Why It’s a Game-Changer
* No other football manager game has real physics for matches. This is our USP (Unique Selling Point).
* Players don’t just follow scripts—they react to the ball, opponents, and environment in real time.
How It Works
Feature	Implementation	Impact
Player Movement	Matter.js for realistic acceleration, deceleration, and collisions.	Players stumble, push, and fight for the ball.
Ball Physics	Friction, spin, air resistance, and bounces based on pitch conditions.	No more "teleporting" passes—realistic trajectories.
Tackling & Fouls	Force-based collisions (tackles, shoulder barges).	Fouls, yellow/red cards based on physics (not just RNG).
Stamina System	Players slow down as stamina drops; sprinting costs more.	Tactical depth: Substitute tired players or adjust pressing intensity.
Weather Effects	Rain = slippery ball, slower players. Wind = curved long passes.	Realism: Adapt tactics to conditions.
Player Traits	Weak foot, flair, work rate affect physics (e.g., weak foot = less power).	No two players feel the same.
Set Pieces	Manual control (drag to aim free kicks, penalties, corners).	Skill-based, not just RNG.
Visual Polish
* Smooth animations (sprinting, sliding, shooting, celebrating).
* Camera angles: Tactical (top-down), TV-style (side-on), or first-person (player POV).
* Replays: Instant highlights (goals, saves, fouls) with slow-mo and multiple angles.

3. AI OPPONENTS (SMARTER THAN ANY COMPETITOR)
AI Manager Personalities
Personality	Playstyle	Weakness
Attacking	High pressing, fast transitions	Vulnerable to counter-attacks
Defensive	Park the bus, long balls	Struggles with possession
Possession-Based	Tiki-taka, short passes	Slow buildup, weak in air
Counter-Attacking	Fast breaks, direct play	Weak in midfield battles
Balanced	Adaptive, no clear weakness	Predictable in big games
AI Adapts to You
* If you always play possession, the AI will press harder.
* If you rely on long balls, the AI will drop deeper.
* If you substitute a player often, the AI will target your weakest link.
AI "Cheating" (But Fair)
* No unfair advantages—AI uses the same physics and rules as you.
* AI mistakes: Misses sitter chances, makes bad subs, just like real managers.

